  						<table border='0' cellpadding='5' width='92%'>
  <tr>
    <td colspan='2' bgcolor='0e024d' class='spti2' valign='top' align='left'>SNEAK
    </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='25%' class='db' valign='top' align='left'>
      <b>Class:</b>
    </td>
    <td width='75%' class='db' valign='top' align='left'>Monk
    </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='25%' class='db' valign='top' align='left'>
      <b>Skill Type:</b>
    </td>
    <td width='75%' class='db' valign='top' align='left'>General
    </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='25%' class='db' valign='top' align='left'>
      <b>Obtained at Level:</b>
    </td>
    <td width='75%' class='db' valign='top' align='left'>8
    </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='25%' class='db' valign='top' align='left'>
      <b>Requires Training:</b>
    </td>
    <td width='75%' class='db' valign='top' align='left'>Yes
    </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='25%' class='db' valign='top' align='left'>
      <b>Formula for Level Cap:</b>
    </td>
    <td width='75%' class='db' valign='top' align='left'>5 + (5 x Level)
    </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='25%' class='db' valign='top' align='left'>
      <b>Skill Cap From Level 1 to 50:</b>
    </td>
    <td width='75%' class='db' valign='top' align='left'>113
    </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='25%' class='db' valign='top' align='left'>
      <b>Skill Cap From Level 51 to 60:</b>
    </td>
    <td width='75%' class='db' valign='top' align='left'>113
    </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='25%' class='db' valign='top' align='left'>
      <b>Description:</b>
    </td>
    <td width='75%' class='db' valign='top' align='left'>Unlike hide, sneak enables you to move and still remain hidden.  A rogue who is sneaking is both invisible to undead and non-undead.
    </td>
  </tr>
</table>
<table border='0' cellpadding='5' width='92%'>
  <tr>
    <td width='25%' class='db' valign='top' align='left'>
      <b>Related Skills:</b>
    </td>
    <td width='75%' class='db' valign='top' align='left'>
<li><a href='skilldetails.asp?Id=341&Class=Monk&Category=General'>Forage</a></li>
<li><a href='skilldetails.asp?Id=234&Class=Monk&Category=General'>Safe Fall</a></li>
    </td>
  </tr>
    <tr>
      <td colspan=2>
  <table border='0' width='100%' cellspacing='0' cellpadding='5'>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 bgcolor='#000066' class='spti2'>SKILL COMMENTS</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>SNEAK WITH OR WITHOUT HIDE</span><b>, By Malky</b> <small>(7/3/2001)</small><br><br>Rogues can use both Hide and Sneak at the same time, alowing them to move invisibly. The rest of us only reduce the agro range of the back side of mobs.<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>TWO DIFFERENT SKILLS MONK IS NOT ROGUE</span><b>, By Leelyth</b> <small>(1/28/2001)</small><br><br>Two sneak types? Rogues move hidden while sneaking. Monks reduce aggro range while they are not in the line of sight.<P>
I played both; and they are indeed different (halflings get the same sneaking as rogue though; but they can only know if they are successful; or progress if they are rogues)<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>SNEAKING IS LOS BASED</span><b>, By Kinjaro</b> <small>(1/28/2001)</small><br><br>     Think of sneaking as tip-toeing around so mobs can't hear you.  If you sneak behind one, it has no way of knowing that you are there.  However, if you wander into the mob's aggro radius while in its line of sight, it will invariably attack you (most likely because you look so foolish trying to be quiet when it can see you ).  An easy way to see if sneak has worked is to con the monster.  If it is indifferent while you are behind it, sneak was sucessful and you can move on.  If not, wait for it to recycle and try again.<P>
     As a side note, if you use sneak behind vendors that would not normally sell to you, you can buy and sell from them as you normally would.  Quite useful in certain dungeons (Runnyeye and Sol A come to mind), as you can sell heavy weapons off instead of leaving them to rot, making dungeon runs far more profitable for you.<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>NOT HIDDEN</span><b>, By Tepes</b> <small>(1/28/2001)</small><br><br>Not hidden at all - see entries under rogue for more info. Sneak reduces the aggro/frenzy range on a mob, allowing you to move closer to it without being jumped - or, as long as you approach from behind, walk right up and (well, a rogue would BS it)<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>YEP, I THINK YOU ARE HIDDEN</span><b>, By Djim</b> <small>(1/28/2001)</small><br><br>When Sneaking I think there are two modes.(successful, and 'I think I am sneaking')  If you are successful you are totally invisible. I have done wardances around skellies on the FOB with this, and not been noticed. If you are not successful then you are not informed in any way and are still visible.  The big problem is if you are not successful it does NOT inform you of your lack of success.  Useful, but not trustworthy.<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='50%' align='left' valign='top'>&nbsp;</td>
      <td width='50%' align='right' valign='top' class='db2'><a href=skilldetails.asp?Id=233&Class=Monk&Category=General&Page=2>Next Page</a></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db2'><b>Click <a href=skilldetails.asp?Action=Comment&Id=233&Class=Monk&Category=General>here</a> to have your own say.</td>
    </tr>
